The paper discusses a solution for privacy concerns in DNA sequencing, which involves separating the process of reading fragments and assembling reads. This suggests a focus on security and privacy, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a trusted local data collector, which could involve database management (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the selection of coverage depth, which could involve computational engineering (cs.CE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
